---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="AI Project Brain Lab — Pablo Suzarte"
  description="An AI and education project by Pablo Suzarte about designing context, continuity, and structure for serious AI collaboration."
  lang="en"
>
  <header class="project-nav">
    <div class="project-nav-inner">
      <a href="/" class="nav-back">← Back</a>
      <a href="/" class="nav-logo">PS</a>
      <span class="nav-breadcrumb">AI & Education</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="project-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="project-meta">AI & Education · Self-initiated product concept · 2026</p>
      <h1 class="project-title">AI Project Brain Lab</h1>
      <p class="project-tagline">
        A course-led product concept about turning AI from a clever tool into a real project collaborator.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-metrics">
        <div class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-value">08</span>
          <span class="metric-label">teaching chapters</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-value">05</span>
          <span class="metric-label">core system layers</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-value">01</span>
          <span class="metric-label">portfolio page inside pablosuzarte.com</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="future-role-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="future-role-panel">
        <div class="future-role-copy">
          <p class="project-meta">Designing Project Intelligence</p>
          <h2 class="future-role-title">A future role for people who design how humans and AI think together.</h2>
          <p class="future-role-text">
            The focus of this master-program-style website is not only to explain a framework. It is to help people build a new mindset from 0 to 100 and design their own project intelligence.
          </p>
          <p class="future-role-text">
            At the center of that role is a simple idea: a project brain is not a folder of notes. It is an operating system for human-AI collaboration.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="future-role-stack">
          <article class="info-card">
            <p class="card-label">Role definition</p>
            <h3>Single source of truth logic designer</h3>
            <p>
              Someone who turns repeated friction into the right file, structure, and workflow layer so serious projects can continue with clarity and low cognitive friction.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="info-card">
            <p class="card-label">Operating rule</p>
            <h3>Structure should emerge from friction</h3>
            <p>
              If friction appears repeatedly, create the file or structure that solves that friction. Real projects teach what structure is necessary.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="future-role-rules">
        <article class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-value">05</span>
          <span class="metric-label">minimum viable stack: CLAUDE, status, evidence, assets, working style</span>
        </article>
        <article class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-value">01</span>
          <span class="metric-label">job per file: every layer has one clear responsibility</span>
        </article>
        <article class="metric-card">
          <span class="metric-value">∞</span>
          <span class="metric-label">the system grows only when repeated friction proves a new layer is needed</span>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="label-num">01</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Overview</h2>
        <div class="accent-line"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p class="lead">
          AI Project Brain Lab is where I explore the overlap between AI, UX, systems thinking, and education.
        </p>
        <p>
          The project started from a simple observation: most AI workflows look impressive in the moment, but collapse when a project becomes complex, collaborative, and long-running.
        </p>
        <p>
          Instead of teaching prompting as a trick, I shaped this as a course concept about context design, continuity, and project structure. The result is both a teaching product and a portfolio artifact for how I think about future-facing design work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="label-num">02</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Problem</h2>
        <div class="accent-line"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="card-grid">
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>Context disappears</h3>
            <p>People keep rebuilding the same background instead of building momentum across sessions.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>Continuity breaks</h3>
            <p>Good thinking gets lost between notes, tools, and decisions, which makes serious work hard to continue.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>Outputs stay shallow</h3>
            <p>AI can sound useful in moments, but it often fails when a project needs memory, judgment, and structure over time.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="label-num">03</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Shift</h2>
        <div class="accent-line"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="card-grid card-grid--two">
          <article class="info-card">
            <p class="card-label">Old mode</p>
            <h3>Reactive AI use</h3>
            <ul class="plain-list">
              <li>Ask isolated questions</li>
              <li>Hope the output fits</li>
              <li>Repeat project context constantly</li>
              <li>Lose clarity between sessions</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="info-card info-card--accent">
            <p class="card-label">New mode</p>
            <h3>Designed AI collaboration</h3>
            <ul class="plain-list">
              <li>Design context deliberately</li>
              <li>Build continuity into the workflow</li>
              <li>Separate evidence, status, and decisions clearly</li>
              <li>Guide intelligence across time</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="label-num">04</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">System</h2>
        <div class="accent-line"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p class="lead">
          The core teaching device is a five-layer project brain that makes serious AI collaboration more usable.
        </p>
        <div class="layer-grid">
          <article class="info-card">
            <p class="card-label">CLAUDE.md</p>
            <p>Defines the project worldview, intent, and reasoning path.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="info-card">
            <p class="card-label">PROJECT_STATUS.md</p>
            <p>Makes progress, current state, and next steps legible.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="info-card">
            <p class="card-label">EVIDENCE_PACK.md</p>
            <p>Separates grounded proof from loose opinion.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="info-card">
            <p class="card-label">ASSET_INVENTORY.md</p>
            <p>Tracks what exists so the work can build on real material.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="info-card">
            <p class="card-label">WORKING_STYLE.md</p>
            <p>Clarifies tone, collaboration preferences, and execution standards.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="label-num">05</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">What I Designed</h2>
        <div class="accent-line"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <ul class="plain-list">
          <li>Course positioning and concept framing</li>
          <li>Landing-page narrative and conversion structure</li>
          <li>Teaching language for AI, continuity, and project intelligence</li>
          <li>A portfolio-native presentation for the project inside pablosuzarte.com</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="label-num">06</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Why It Matters</h2>
        <div class="accent-line"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="card-grid">
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>It extends my portfolio beyond delivery work</h3>
            <p>This project shows how I think when the task is not only to ship a product, but to define a new capability and teach it clearly.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>It connects AI and leadership</h3>
            <p>The focus is not automation for its own sake. It is about designing better conditions for people, teams, and tools to work together.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>It positions education as product design</h3>
            <p>The course concept is treated as a product system: audience, promise, structure, proof, and experience all had to work together.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container cta-block">
      <p class="card-label">AI Project Brain Lab</p>
      <h2>Part of pablosuzarte.com, not a side experiment.</h2>
      <p>
        This page is the portfolio home for the project. If you want to talk about AI, education, or how this could evolve into a real product, get in touch.
      </p>
      <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary">Let’s talk ↗</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .section {
    padding: 7rem 0;
  }

  .section-alt {
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  .section-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .section-label {
    position: sticky;
    top: 100px;
  }

  .label-num {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .accent-line {
    width: 32px;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 1px;
  }

  .project-nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 50;
    background: rgba(8, 8, 15, 0.92);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .project-nav-inner {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
    min-height: 64px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .nav-back,
  .nav-logo,
  .nav-breadcrumb {
    color: var(--muted-light);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .nav-logo {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .project-hero {
    padding: 7rem 0 4rem;
  }

  .future-role-hero {
    padding: 0 0 5rem;
  }

  .future-role-panel {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.25fr) minmax(320px, 0.75fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .future-role-copy,
  .future-role-stack {
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.75rem;
  }

  .future-role-stack {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .future-role-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.2rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .future-role-text {
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .future-role-rules {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .project-meta {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .project-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .project-tagline,
  .section-body p,
  .plain-list li {
    color: var(--muted-light);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .project-tagline,
  .lead {
    max-width: 64ch;
  }

  .lead {
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-metrics,
  .card-grid,
  .layer-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-metrics {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .card-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .card-grid--two {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .layer-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .metric-card,
  .info-card,
  .cta-block {
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
  }

  .metric-card {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .metric-value {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .metric-label {
    color: var(--muted-light);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .info-card {
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .info-card--accent {
    border-color: rgba(100, 255, 218, 0.25);
  }

  .info-card h3 {
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .card-label {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .plain-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .plain-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  .plain-list li::before {
    content: '▸';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.05rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
  }

  .cta-block {
    padding: 2rem;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .cta-block h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cta-block p {
    max-width: 58ch;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--bg);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .section-grid,
    .hero-metrics,
    .future-role-panel,
    .future-role-rules,
    .card-grid,
    .card-grid--two,
    .layer-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .section-label {
      position: static;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .container,
    .project-nav-inner {
      padding: 0 1.25rem;
    }

    .nav-breadcrumb {
      display: none;
    }
  }
</style>
